ic politics of diversity, discontinuity, and exodus will find Fugitive Rousseau indispensable.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aPrimitivism. 0aSlavery. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aEnlightenment.  aJean-Jacques.  aRousseau.  aempire.  afreedom.  ainternational political theory.  apolitical resistance.  aprimitivism.  aradical democratic theory.  aslavery.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311072903040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823257324zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823257324423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823257324/original  a978-3-11-072903-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK